parameters: \n<???>So,\. how have you been?
\n<???>It's been a while since we last saw each other.
You look to your left.
You're at Nutmeg Bowl.\. Allen is talking to you for the
first time.\. Beck, Will Dwyer, and Max are in the
background.
\n<???>How have you been holding up, Seb?
\n<???>Look at your friends.\. Aren't they great?
You look to your right.
You're in genetics class,\. sitting next to Beck, Allen,
and Logan.\. You're sharing a google document for the
class assignment.
\n<???>These are your friends who are leaving.
\n<???>Will is going to New York.\. Allen is staying in
Connecticut,\. but won't be as available.
\n<???>And Beck...\. well I think you know by now where he's
going.
You look to your left.
Will Merwin is showing you and Juan a cursed video at
the freshman social.\. It's not much,\. but it's the
beginning of a friend group.
\n<???>I know it can seem like your senior year is going to
be empty without them.
\n<???>But look at your other friends.
\n<???>They've stuck with you through thick and thin at St.
Joes.
\n<???>You still have a year of memories to make with them.\.
Why waste it?
You look to your right.
You and Waliullah are in the Courtyard,\. talking about
girls you like,\. despite the nervousness.
\n<???>I know it can seem like you're alone,\. separate from
the trio of Allen, Beck, and Will.
\n<???>I know it can feel like everything is changing.
\n<???>But your best friend since freshman year,\. Waliullah,\.
is on this journey with you.
\n<???>He believes that senior year is going to be worth it.\.
Don't you trust him?
You look to your right.
You're at a fancy bowling alley.\. You've just got word
that your team ranked 6th in the state,\. and you're
celebrating with your senior friends.
\n<???>I know the \c[10]fear\c[0] got to you last time.
\n<???>I don't blame you.\. I know it's hard to overcome.
You look to your left.
You're in the basement of Connor's house.\. It's the
last day of Drama Club.\. There's laughing,
congratulating, and crying...\. a lot of crying.
You're not crying,\. but nobody's judging you for that.\.
You're all in this together\. - you're a community.
\n<???>I just hope that...\. when the time comes...
\n<???>You make the right decision.
You look to your left.
It's all of you\. - not your old friends or your new
friends, but just your friends\. - hanging out in the
cafe after school.\.\. It's just a normal day.
\n<???>Your journey is coming to an end, Seb.
\n<???>It's not too long until you'll have a decision to
make.
\n<???>Just remember...
\n<???>You're not on your own.
\n<???>This place may not be real,\. but your friends are.
\n<???>I'll see you, Seb.
LittleLad left the party.
